<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1437,861,1393]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,437,861,888]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Recognition characters:</emphasis>
Dark brown species; 
<quantity box="[681,805,861,888]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.75" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.5" pageId="48" pageNumber="49" unit="mm" value="17.5" valueMax="20.0" valueMin="15.0">15–20 mm</quantity>
; mystax with black bristles above and white or pale yellowish ones below; thorax clothed with yellowish dust; wings with reddish aspect, especially at the apex and along the posterior margin, veins often with hyaline margin; abdomen clothed with dust so as to give it a dark brown color, posterior margins of segments slightly lighter; femora with a preapical reddish band, front and middle tibiae with an annulus near the middle and black apex, metatarsus mostly yellow, black at the apex, other tarsal segments mostly black, usually narrowly yellowish at the base; hind tibiae mostly infuscated, but always a narrow basal space is yellowish.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="48.[151,1437,861,1393]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,355,1113,1140]" pageId="48" pageNumber="49">Distribution:</emphasis>
